rComments: the final mark composed of such a small number of tests and assignments which is graded really hard and in class she never really helps properly she just translates different texts. So going to her class is waste of time since she's not helpful and won't even prepare you for the test.

Her lectures are composed of her reading essay-length notes off of a paper. She does not give examples. She is monotone and very quiet. Her lecture notes that she posts are in an essay format. If you ask a question she is very hostile with her answers. Some of the things she says during lectures are very off topic and she may put it on the exam.
All she does is read off her notes in class. So, beware. You WILL get bored.

One of the best profs in the UTSC faculty, by far! She depends very heavily on the textbook, so if you read the chapters before her lectures you will be set.  Very fair marker. Make use of her office hours, she is a very nice lady, very approachable. I really enjoyed her class.

She is a one of a kind prof. Honestly, she walked out on my class writing a midterm which obv led to people cheating. ALL of us there4 had to rewrite OR have a final worth 55%. She DOES NOT explain her expectations until after you get your grade back. She is a nice person but not prof material. She started using portal this year but not much else.

The worst prof I have ever had. Gives little explanation/instruction for anything (exams, assignments) Only tells you what she wanted/expected AFTER handing things back. HUGE packages of readings to do. No technology use (i.e. no power points) Lectures are very unstructured and hard to follow/take notes. I don't recommend taking a course with her!
Awful prof. She doesn't use the internet or technology at all. No text books but hands out a massive amount of readings. Goes way off topic majority of the time. Just bad.
She has clear favorites and does not even mask it. Her participation percentage is way too high.

Great teacher! Goes out of her way to help students. Very caring. Do your part, show interest and she'll do her part. She will expect you to work hard because she cares a lot for her students. Develops that important gut feeling necessary for translation. I strongly recommend this professor. But remember, work hard and show it.
She is so much nicer this year than last year..and more organized...and more willing to help students. What happened?

Sylvia Mittler is a good teacher but she stopped caring i think. She doesn't like to help students and her outlines are near to useless. She's a good prof but her material are disorganized but i enjoyed her class

Worst french teacher I have ever had.  She tends to give more attention to students who are already good in french and seems to be annoyed with those that need the help. Asking for her help will only discourage you from persuing french any further.
